sentences: Olga Bell (born Olga Balashova, Russian: Ольга Балашова, 3 October 1983) is an American musician, music producer, composer, and singer-songwriter.
In 2016, Bell released her third studio album Tempo.

In August 2005, having graduated from the New England Conservatory but not been accepted to the Juilliard School's graduate program, Bell moved to New York City to pursue music outside the classical realm.
From 2005 to 2010, Bell split her time between piano teaching and theater accompaniment gigs and pursuing her new musical project on the side.
In 2007, they self-produced and self-released the six-song Bell EP.
In 2011, with Chiavaro and McMurray having left the band, Bell worked with Jason Nazary and Gunnar Olsen to produce and release her first full-length album, Diamonite.
In 2009 she was selected by composer Osvaldo Golijov and soprano Dawn Upshaw for a workshop and concert at Carnegie Hall.
In 2011, Bell received the Jerome Fund Grant from the American Composers Forum to aid in the completion of her first large-scale composition Край (Krai).
The album was released to critical acclaim in 2014, following a sold-out live premiere at the Walker Art Center in Minneapolis.
In 2013, she directed a video for their single Oyster.
From 2011 to 2013, Bell toured as a keyboardist and vocalist for Chairlift and Dirty Projectors.
Incitation was released on 16 October 2015.
"On 9 March 2016, Bell released "Randomness", which Pitchfork named Best New Track.
After releasing videos for "Randomness" and "ATA", Bell announced that Tempo, her third full-length album would be released on 27 May 2016.
"In the summer of 2016, Bell toured in the U.S. and Europe supporting Chairlift, Empress Of, and Yeasayer.

On 12 August 2015, Nowness premiered the video for "Goalie", the last track on Incitation, which Bell co-directed with Christina Ladwig.

In mid-2015, Bell toured with Son Lux and premiered live versions of songs from Incitation, an EP she released on One Little Indian Records later that year, and Tempo, a full-length album to be released the following year.
2013-15: Край (Krai) and Nothankyou

During the same period as Край's recording, Bell pursued side project Nothankyou with British musician Tom Vek, releasing three dance tracks between 2012-14 through Moshi Moshi Records and independently on Soundcloud.
She was born in Moscow, Russia, raised in Anchorage, Alaska and is currently based in Brooklyn, New York.
Bell started playing the piano at age seven, after moving with her mother from Moscow to Anchorage, Alaska and made her public debut two years later.
=== 2005-13: Beginnings and Diamonite ===
Consequence of Sound remarked that "while moments on Diamonite might recall other artists, the band never sounds imitative or even descendant of those influences".
